episodes.synopsis: The team investigates a number of reports regarding strange lights seen in the sky by more than 30 people in two Texas towns.
episodes.title: Texas is for Sightings

episodes.synopsis: The team visits the San Luis Valley, home to decades of UFO reports, to investigate animal mutilations and meet a survivor of alien abduction.
episodes.title: Alien Cowboys

episodes.synopsis: In Roswell, New Mexico, the epicenter of UFO activity, the team sees a video of an alleged UFO crash and investigates the site of the incident.
episodes.title: UFO Landing Zone?

episodes.synopsis: Since 1993, residents in the Phoenix area have reported sightings of mammoth wedge-shaped objects, and the evidence includes a convincing video.
episodes.title: Abducted in Arizona

episodes.synopsis: Are the objects that appear in the night sky over Central California (and sometimes follow residents) of government or extraterrestrial origin?
episodes.title: Dirty Secrets

episodes.synopsis: The team travels to Florida to investigate numerous sightings of objects that appeared to follow the Space Shuttle as it left the launch pad.
episodes.title: Games of Drones

episodes.synopsis: Ryder, Ben and James brave the Brazilian jungle to hunt for alien crash survivors reportedly hiding out near the "Roswell of South America."
episodes.title: Alien Castaways

episodes.synopsis: In Mexico, the team splits on identifying the body of an alien infant and see video of an alleged mothership releasing multiple craft into the sky.
episodes.title: Alien Baby Farm

video.title: Chasing UFOs
video.synopsis: An elite group of experts travels across the country investigating reports of UFO sightings, alien abductions and government cover-ups.
